    <content>
        <description>
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Safety Labeling Standard Overview</title>
                <para>
                    This Data Module defines the safety labeling standards for the AMPEL360 Q100 
                    BWB hydrogen-hybrid aircraft program. It establishes a consistent hierarchy 
                    of warnings, cautions, and notes with specific focus on hydrogen-related 
                    hazards unique to the Q100 propulsion system.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Purpose:</emphasis> To ensure consistent 
                    communication of safety-critical information across all technical publications, 
                    maintenance procedures, and operational documents.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Scope:</emphasis> Covers all safety message 
                    types, hydrogen-specific hazard symbols, typography standards, color coding, 
                    and S1000D markup requirements.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Severity Hierarchy</title>
                <para>
                    The Q100 program uses a three-level severity hierarchy based on ISO 3864 
                    and ANSI Z535.4 standards:
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>WARNING</title>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> Indicates a hazard 
                        with a medium level of risk which, if not avoided, could result in death 
                        or serious injury.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Usage Criteria:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Potential for fatality or permanent injury</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Immediate danger to personnel</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>High-energy hazards (electrical, mechanical, thermal)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Hazardous material exposure</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Visual Format:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Element</entry>
                                    <entry>Specification</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Signal Word</entry>
                                    <entry>WARNING (all capitals)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Color</entry>
                                    <entry>Orange background (#FF6600), Black text</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>Triangular hazard symbol with exclamation mark</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Font Weight</entry>
                                    <entry>Bold for signal word, regular for message</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100-Specific Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>warning</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>CRYOGENIC BURN HAZARD. Liquid hydrogen at -253°C (-423°F). 
                                Contact with skin causes severe frostbite and tissue damage. Wear 
                                insulated cryogenic gloves and face shield when handling LH₂ lines 
                                and fittings.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>warning</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>FLAMMABLE GAS HAZARD. Hydrogen has wide flammability range 
                                (4-75% in air). Invisible flame. Ensure adequate ventilation. No 
                                ignition sources within 25 feet of venting operations. Use hydrogen 
                                detector before entering enclosed spaces.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>warning</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>HIGH PRESSURE HAZARD. Hydrogen storage at 350-700 bar 
                                (5,000-10,000 psi). Explosive decompression risk. Verify pressure 
                                gauge readings before disconnecting any fitting. Use torque wrench 
                                per torque specifications.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>warning</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>HIGH VOLTAGE HAZARD. Fuel cell system operates at ±270 VDC+. 
                                Lethal shock hazard. De-energize system and verify zero voltage 
                                before maintenance. Use insulated tools rated for 600V minimum. 
                                Lock out / tag out required.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>warning</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>ASPHYXIATION HAZARD. Hydrogen displaces oxygen. Oxygen 
                                deficient atmosphere can cause unconsciousness without warning. 
                                Monitor oxygen levels continuously in confined spaces. Maintain 
                                minimum 19.5% oxygen concentration. Use breathing apparatus if 
                                oxygen level drops below 19.5%.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>CAUTION</title>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> Indicates a hazard 
                        with a low level of risk which, if not avoided, could result in minor or 
                        moderate injury, or damage to equipment.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Usage Criteria:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Potential for minor injury (cuts, bruises, minor burns)</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Equipment damage risk</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Performance degradation</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Procedural errors with recoverable consequences</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Visual Format:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Element</entry>
                                    <entry>Specification</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Signal Word</entry>
                                    <entry>CAUTION (all capitals)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Color</entry>
                                    <entry>Yellow background (#FFCC00), Black text</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>Triangular hazard symbol with exclamation mark</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Font Weight</entry>
                                    <entry>Bold for signal word, regular for message</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100-Specific Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>caution</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>Do not exceed maximum boil-off rate of 0.5% per day. Excessive 
                                boil-off indicates insulation degradation. Monitor tank pressure and 
                                temperature continuously during ground operations.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <warningAndCautionPara>
                            <warningAndCautionType>caution</warningAndCautionType>
                            <warningAndCautionInfo>
                                <para>Do not over-torque cryogenic fittings. Use torque wrench with 
                                specified values (15-20 Nm for AN-4 fittings). Over-torquing damages 
                                seals and causes leaks.</para>
                            </warningAndCautionInfo>
                        </warningAndCautionPara>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>NOTE</title>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Definition:</emphasis> Provides important 
                        information for optimal performance, efficiency, or understanding. Does 
                        not indicate hazard.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Usage Criteria:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <randomList>
                            <listItem><para>Best practices and recommendations</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Performance optimization tips</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Explanatory information</para></listItem>
                            <listItem><para>Cross-references to related procedures</para></listItem>
                        </randomList>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Visual Format:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Element</entry>
                                    <entry>Specification</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Signal Word</entry>
                                    <entry>NOTE (all capitals)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Color</entry>
                                    <entry>Blue background (#0066CC), White text</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>Information icon (lowercase 'i' in circle)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Font Weight</entry>
                                    <entry>Bold for signal word, regular for message</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Q100-Specific Examples:</emphasis>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        NOTE: Fuel cell efficiency peaks at 60% rated power. Operating below 
                        40% or above 90% rated power reduces efficiency and increases thermal 
                        stress on membrane.
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        NOTE: Zero-boil-off cryocooler consumes approximately 2 kW during ground 
                        operations. Include in ground power budget calculations.
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>H₂-Specific Hazard Symbols</title>
                <para>
                    The following standardized hazard symbols are used for hydrogen-related 
                    warnings on the Q100 aircraft:
                </para>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="4">
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry>Symbol ID</entry>
                                <entry>Hazard Type</entry>
                                <entry>ISO Reference</entry>
                                <entry>Usage Location</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>H2-CRYO-01</entry>
                                <entry>Cryogenic Burn Hazard</entry>
                                <entry>ISO 7010 W040 (modified)</entry>
                                <entry>LH₂ tanks, fill ports, vent lines</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>H2-FLAM-01</entry>
                                <entry>Flammable Gas</entry>
                                <entry>ISO 7010 W021</entry>
                                <entry>H₂ storage, distribution lines</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>H2-PRES-01</entry>
                                <entry>High Pressure</entry>
                                <entry>ISO 7010 W029</entry>
                                <entry>GH₂ cylinders, pressure regulators</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>H2-ASPH-01</entry>
                                <entry>Asphyxiation Hazard</entry>
                                <entry>ISO 7010 W041</entry>
                                <entry>Enclosed fuel cell compartments</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>ELEC-HV-01</entry>
                                <entry>High Voltage (±270 VDC+)</entry>
                                <entry>ISO 7010 W012</entry>
                                <entry>Fuel cell stacks, power electronics</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Typography and Color Standards</title>
                <para>
                    All safety messages must adhere to the following typography and color standards:
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Typography</title>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="3">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Element</entry>
                                    <entry>Font</entry>
                                    <entry>Size</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Signal Word</entry>
                                    <entry>Arial Bold, all caps</entry>
                                    <entry>14-16pt (print), 18-20pt (display)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Message Text</entry>
                                    <entry>Arial Regular</entry>
                                    <entry>10-12pt (print), 14-16pt (display)</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Symbol</entry>
                                    <entry>ISO 7010 standard</entry>
                                    <entry>Minimum 25mm height</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>Color Specifications</title>
                    <table>
                        <tgroup cols="4">
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Level</entry>
                                    <entry>Background</entry>
                                    <entry>Text</entry>
                                    <entry>Border</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>WARNING</entry>
                                    <entry>Orange (#FF6600 / Pantone 021C)</entry>
                                    <entry>Black (#000000)</entry>
                                    <entry>Black 2pt solid</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>CAUTION</entry>
                                    <entry>Yellow (#FFCC00 / Pantone 109C)</entry>
                                    <entry>Black (#000000)</entry>
                                    <entry>Black 2pt solid</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>NOTE</entry>
                                    <entry>Blue (#0066CC / Pantone 2935C)</entry>
                                    <entry>White (#FFFFFF)</entry>
                                    <entry>Blue 2pt solid</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                    <para>
                        <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Accessibility:</emphasis> All color 
                        combinations meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA contrast requirements (minimum 
                        4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text).
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Placement Rules in S1000D Data Modules</title>
                <para>
                    Safety messages must be positioned according to the following rules:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <sequentialList>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Proximity Rule:</emphasis> Place 
                            warning/caution immediately before the step that presents the hazard.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Visibility Rule:</emphasis> Ensure 
                            warning/caution appears on same page as hazardous step (no page breaks).</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Hierarchy Rule:</emphasis> Multiple 
                            warnings/cautions appear in order: WARNING, then CAUTION, then NOTE.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Consolidation Rule:</emphasis> 
                            Multiple warnings of same type may be combined if they relate to the 
                            same step.</para>
                        </listItem>
                        <listItem>
                            <para><emphasis emphasisType="em01">Front Matter Rule:</emphasis> 
                            General warnings applicable to entire procedure appear in dedicated 
                            "Safety Information" section at beginning of data module.</para>
                        </listItem>
                    </sequentialList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>S1000D Markup Examples</title>
                <para>
                    The following markup patterns are used for safety messages in S1000D XML:
                </para>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>WARNING Markup</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;warningAndCautionPara&gt;
  &lt;warningAndCautionType&gt;warning&lt;/warningAndCautionType&gt;
  &lt;warningAndCautionInfo&gt;
    &lt;para&gt;CRYOGENIC BURN HAZARD. Liquid hydrogen at -253°C 
    (-423°F). Contact with skin causes severe frostbite and 
    tissue damage. Wear insulated cryogenic gloves and face 
    shield when handling LH₂ lines and fittings.&lt;/para&gt;
  &lt;/warningAndCautionInfo&gt;
&lt;/warningAndCautionPara&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>CAUTION Markup</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;warningAndCautionPara&gt;
  &lt;warningAndCautionType&gt;caution&lt;/warningAndCautionType&gt;
  &lt;warningAndCautionInfo&gt;
    &lt;para&gt;Do not over-torque cryogenic fittings. Use torque 
    wrench with specified values (15-20 Nm for AN-4 fittings). 
    Over-torquing damages seals and causes leaks.&lt;/para&gt;
  &lt;/warningAndCautionInfo&gt;
&lt;/warningAndCautionPara&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
                
                <levelledPara>
                    <title>NOTE Markup</title>
                    <para>
                        <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs11">
&lt;para&gt;
  &lt;emphasis emphasisType="em02"&gt;NOTE:&lt;/emphasis&gt; Fuel cell 
  efficiency peaks at 60% rated power. Operating below 40% or 
  above 90% rated power reduces efficiency and increases thermal 
  stress on membrane.
&lt;/para&gt;
                        </verbatimText>
                    </para>
                </levelledPara>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Compliance and Standards</title>
                <para>
                    This safety labeling standard complies with the following industry standards:
                </para>
                <para>
                    <randomList>
                        <listItem><para>ISO 3864 - Graphical symbols - Safety colours and safety signs</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>ISO 7010 - Safety signs</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>ANSI Z535.4 - Product Safety Signs and Labels</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>S1000D Issue 5.0 - Safety markup requirements</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>ATA iSpec 2200 - Safety message formats</para></listItem>
                        <listItem><para>WCAG 2.1 Level AA - Web accessibility contrast requirements</para></listItem>
                    </randomList>
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
            
            <levelledPara>
                <title>Usage Notes</title>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Mandatory Compliance:</emphasis> All AMPEL360 
                    Q100 technical publications must follow this safety labeling standard. 
                    Deviations require approval from STK_SAF and STK_CM.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Translation:</emphasis> When translating safety 
                    messages, preserve signal word positioning and color coding. Signal words 
                    translate as: WARNING = AVERTISSEMENT (FR), WARNUNG (DE); CAUTION = ATTENTION 
                    (FR), VORSICHT (DE).
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emphasis emphasisType="em01">Updates:</emphasis> This standard is maintained 
                    by STK_SAF with input from STK_CM and STK_PUB. Check for latest version before 
                    creating new publications.
                </para>
            </levelledPara>
